WEBVTT

00:00.336 --> 00:01.603
MARY JANE: Previously,
on "Being Mary Jane"...

00:01.704 --> 00:03.914
The school board just slashed the budget

00:03.945 --> 00:05.820
for this high school for
the third time this year.

00:05.875 --> 00:07.820
They're diverting funds to a for-profit

00:07.859 --> 00:09.827
private charter school

00:09.897 --> 00:11.639
and the students and
parents are planning

00:11.678 --> 00:13.460
a big protest tomorrow.

00:13.655 --> 00:15.678
This totally ties in
with all the controversy

00:15.717 --> 00:17.834
swirling around the
new Education Secretary,

00:17.873 --> 00:20.107
who is a big supporter of school choice.

00:20.193 --> 00:22.021
- Yeah.
- We should send a team.

00:22.115 --> 00:23.490
Oh, I'm one step ahead of you, mama.

00:23.529 --> 00:25.290
I already convinced Garrett to send you.

00:25.345 --> 00:26.412
So, I'll get to be doing

00:26.489 --> 00:28.089
the hard hitting stories that I want!

00:28.111 --> 00:29.264
Wait. Wait. If I'm out in the field,

00:29.365 --> 00:32.331
who's gonna be taking
my place in my chair?

00:32.386 --> 00:34.651
The anger of the crowd has boiled over

00:34.722 --> 00:36.550
into outright hostility.

00:36.643 --> 00:38.190
The protesters feel the board

00:38.245 --> 00:39.975
simply does not represent their views.

00:40.076 --> 00:41.443
- [head thuds]
- Justin!

00:41.544 --> 00:44.276
- Mary Jane!
- Justin!

00:45.001 --> 00:46.434
Hey, Paul.

00:46.612 --> 00:49.049
Did you know that your
ex-lover was in town?

00:49.151 --> 00:51.633
Frank and I...

00:51.679 --> 00:53.488
it's water under a 40-year-old bridge.

00:53.589 --> 00:58.193
You're a straight out son
of a bitch, Frank Pearl.

00:58.294 --> 01:00.028
You show up at my house

01:00.129 --> 01:03.198
and barely say two words to me?

01:03.299 --> 01:04.232
[scoffs]

01:04.333 --> 01:05.600
I figured that's what you wanted.

01:05.701 --> 01:07.902
What I want is an apology.

01:08.004 --> 01:13.720
I was all set to start a
life with you 44 years ago.

01:13.822 --> 01:17.191
Come on, Helen, we both
know why that didn't happen.

01:17.292 --> 01:18.325
I've said my peace,

01:18.426 --> 01:21.996
and it's probably best to
leave it all in the past.

01:22.097 --> 01:25.466
Seven million people heard
you scream his name live on TV.

01:25.567 --> 01:26.834
It's gone viral,

01:26.935 --> 01:30.037
and now everybody wanna
know who "that" man is.

01:30.138 --> 01:32.973
REPORTERS: [shouting mixed questions]

01:33.074 --> 01:35.309
I think keeping our lives
private may not be possible.

01:35.410 --> 01:36.610
I'm a journalist.

01:36.711 --> 01:38.512
I live by the mantra
that I cover the story,

01:38.613 --> 01:39.613
I don't become the story.

01:39.714 --> 01:40.986
I'm right there with you.

01:41.040 --> 01:42.750
But facing the limelight, honey,

01:42.851 --> 01:44.952
that comes with the territory.

01:45.053 --> 01:47.121
All I'm asking is that
maybe we could do both.

01:47.222 --> 01:48.455
Is that all right?

01:48.557 --> 01:49.690
Yeah.

01:49.791 --> 01:51.258
Let's do both.

01:51.928 --> 01:53.728
♪ My life can get so crazy ♪

01:53.829 --> 01:56.197
♪ But as long as you're right here ♪

01:56.299 --> 01:58.500
♪ None of the gossip, nothing can stop us ♪

01:58.601 --> 02:00.969
♪ I'm wanna love you with no fears ♪

02:01.070 --> 02:03.171
♪ We can do this thing together ♪

02:03.272 --> 02:05.574
♪ Close your eyes and take my hand ♪

02:05.675 --> 02:07.976
♪ 'Cause what we have is something special ♪

02:08.077 --> 02:11.179
♪ Baby let's just take our chance ♪

02:11.280 --> 02:14.549
<i>♪</i>

02:14.650 --> 02:17.152
- JUSTIN: "ProducerBae"?
- Yeah, that's creative.

02:17.253 --> 02:18.787
It's a compliment.

02:18.888 --> 02:20.488
Mm, of what?

02:20.590 --> 02:23.224
They're saying that you're
too hot to be a producer.

02:23.326 --> 02:24.459
Don't fight the pretty, honey.

02:24.560 --> 02:26.661
Ah, so, it's like he's
serious about his job,

02:26.762 --> 02:29.497
you tack a "bae" on it and then
you make his title irrelevant.

02:29.599 --> 02:32.067
Women have been objectified
since the dawn of time.

02:32.168 --> 02:33.935
We do not get to exchange war stories.

02:34.036 --> 02:35.337
Sorry.

02:35.438 --> 02:37.439
But there is one way to solidify

02:37.540 --> 02:40.475
our relationship on social media...

02:40.576 --> 02:42.644
- Dog face filter.
- [phone camera clicks]

02:42.745 --> 02:43.778
JUSIN: What is that?

02:43.879 --> 02:46.377
Oh, look at that sweet
face. Look at you.

02:46.816 --> 02:49.818
I'm so glad to know that
my high school classmate

02:49.919 --> 02:52.354
ChattyCathy 28, who I haven't seen

02:52.455 --> 02:55.256
since she was blowing a
tuba on the 50 yard line,

02:55.358 --> 02:58.093
will now get to see me
like that on social media.

02:58.194 --> 02:59.327
You were in the band?

02:59.428 --> 03:01.062
Point guard, but I
went to football games.

03:01.163 --> 03:03.131
So, you were a point
guard and prom king?

03:03.232 --> 03:04.599
Prince, actually.

03:04.700 --> 03:06.468
But I would have been
preferred to have been

03:06.569 --> 03:08.136
voted "most likely to succeed."

03:08.237 --> 03:09.237
You're one of those annoying people

03:09.338 --> 03:10.805
who did it all, aren't you?

03:10.906 --> 03:12.440
Actually, no.

03:12.541 --> 03:14.609
You know what? Maybe I should
just check with ChattyCathy 28.

03:14.710 --> 03:15.877
Feel free.

03:15.978 --> 03:17.712
You know, she hasn't
stopped posting about me

03:17.813 --> 03:19.414
ever since we, uh, went public.

03:19.515 --> 03:21.383
That's because we're
connecting with viewers.

03:21.484 --> 03:22.984
We put our relationship out there,

03:23.085 --> 03:25.954
and we're showing people
what a happy, positive,

03:26.055 --> 03:28.356
successful Black couple looks like.

03:29.925 --> 03:32.127
What about...

03:32.228 --> 03:33.995
- George and Senovia?
- Who?

03:34.096 --> 03:36.197
They are my 80-year-old neighbors,

03:36.298 --> 03:39.234
and they are insanely happy.

03:39.335 --> 03:40.568
And you know what?

03:40.670 --> 03:43.138
They don't even know what Twitter is.

03:43.247 --> 03:44.714
The ratings are up.

03:44.807 --> 03:47.226
Garrett is over the moon.

03:47.320 --> 03:49.054
And I see that he's been treating you

03:49.076 --> 03:50.143
like his golden ticket

03:50.167 --> 03:51.567
ever since people found out about us.

03:51.613 --> 03:53.180
Lately, he's been giving
the big assignments

03:53.236 --> 03:54.803
to Kara and other producers.

03:54.809 --> 03:55.809
Maybe it's...

03:55.867 --> 03:57.738
And I understand he is doing that

03:57.765 --> 03:59.030
because he wants me
doing photo ops with you.

03:59.069 --> 04:00.569
Now that kinda thing might get ratings,

04:00.599 --> 04:01.699
and we need those

04:01.715 --> 04:03.283
to solidify your place in the chair.

04:03.298 --> 04:04.364
Exactly.

04:04.380 --> 04:06.080
But it doesn't give me the EP spot.

04:07.363 --> 04:10.799
Then we need to keep what we
post on social media on check.

04:10.900 --> 04:15.603
I mean, would you be okay
with a more curated approach?

04:15.705 --> 04:18.540
My Snapchat will disappear in 24 hours,

04:18.641 --> 04:21.375
and then #ProducerBae...

04:21.476 --> 04:23.745
will be mine and only mine.

04:23.846 --> 04:25.080
Mmm...

04:25.181 --> 04:27.115
- That sweet face.
- Look at that sweet face.

04:27.216 --> 04:28.349
- Mmm, yeah.
- [kisses]

04:28.451 --> 04:33.388
♪ I've got a crush on you ♪

04:33.489 --> 04:36.291
- ♪ Sweetie pie ♪
- [telephone ringing]

04:36.392 --> 04:39.160
♪ All day and nighttime ♪

04:39.261 --> 04:42.130
♪ Give me a sign ♪

04:42.231 --> 04:43.198
[phone continues ringing]

04:43.299 --> 04:46.935
♪ I never had the least notion ♪

04:47.036 --> 04:49.537
♪ That I could fall ♪

04:49.638 --> 04:52.874
HELEN: Oh, those damn telemarketers.

04:52.975 --> 04:55.310
Dinner's almost ready.

04:55.411 --> 04:58.179
[chopping vegetables]

04:58.280 --> 05:00.215
♪ Could you care ♪

05:00.316 --> 05:03.084
♪ For a cunning cottage ♪

05:03.185 --> 05:06.020
♪ Can't wait to kick off my shoes ♪

05:06.122 --> 05:07.789
♪ Strip outta this suit ♪

05:07.890 --> 05:09.324
- ♪ Crash on the couch ♪
- _

05:09.425 --> 05:14.729
♪ And relax my heavy mind ♪

05:14.830 --> 05:18.066
- ♪ Relax my heavy eyes ♪
- KARA: [laughing]

05:18.167 --> 05:19.501
- ♪ And if someone decides to call ♪
-  _

05:19.602 --> 05:22.270
- ♪ I'ma reject it and turn it off ♪
-  _

05:22.371 --> 05:24.305
♪ Uh huh uh ♪

05:24.406 --> 05:26.207
♪ Don't break my peace ♪

05:26.308 --> 05:30.545
♪ I want serenity ♪

05:30.646 --> 05:33.648
- [blows kiss]
- ♪ Heavy mind ♪

05:33.749 --> 05:36.184
PEOPLE IN VIDEO:
[talking over each other]

05:36.285 --> 05:38.586
[knock at door]

05:40.956 --> 05:42.490
[remote clicks]

05:44.426 --> 05:46.327
[knocking continues]

05:47.196 --> 05:49.364
- Hey, ladies.
- Hey! Hey!

05:49.465 --> 05:51.533
Gosh, what are you guys doing here?

05:51.634 --> 05:54.335
- Oh, we miss our men.
- So much.

05:54.436 --> 05:57.372
I know, but I'm kind of
"in" for the night, already.

05:57.473 --> 05:59.407
That's exactly why we came to you.

05:59.508 --> 06:00.875
We're gonna let you sit here

06:00.976 --> 06:03.444
and wallow in your lonesome
while our men are away.

06:03.546 --> 06:05.647
Oh, and we heard about your father.

06:05.748 --> 06:08.116
So sorry. Our deepest condolences.

06:08.217 --> 06:09.551
Thank you.

06:09.652 --> 06:11.519
Well, and I've already
had a string of guests

06:11.620 --> 06:13.521
since the funeral, so, I actually...

06:13.622 --> 06:16.424
I don't mind a little
alone time, you know, so...

06:16.525 --> 06:17.725
We're sorry, Kara.

06:17.827 --> 06:19.627
If you wanna be alone,
we can reschedule this.

06:19.728 --> 06:21.563
- No, no, no, no.
- Kara needs to be with us.

06:21.664 --> 06:24.199
We have way more experience
when it comes to this.

06:24.300 --> 06:25.366
Just trust us, sweetie.

06:25.467 --> 06:26.901
I'm not even dressed to go out.

06:27.002 --> 06:28.837
What makes you think
we're going anywhere?

06:28.938 --> 06:30.171
You guys wore that

06:30.272 --> 06:31.906
to come and drink
champagne in my living room?

06:32.007 --> 06:33.308
Yeah, we can't just take selfies

06:33.409 --> 06:35.076
in our sweatpants and
footie pajamas now can we?

06:35.177 --> 06:36.311
Oh, no.

06:36.412 --> 06:37.679
Anyway, you can decide where

06:37.780 --> 06:39.113
we're having drinks tomorrow night.

06:39.215 --> 06:40.315
LAUREN: Mm, yeah.

06:40.416 --> 06:41.783
Oh, we're hangin' out
tomorrow night, too?

06:41.884 --> 06:44.085
It makes the week go by so much faster.

06:44.186 --> 06:46.387
We'll let Heidi have her champagne.

06:46.488 --> 06:50.892
This is for you and me.

06:50.993 --> 06:52.260
Oh.

06:52.361 --> 06:53.962
LAUREN: Mm-hm.

06:54.063 --> 06:54.996
All right.

06:55.097 --> 06:56.264
HEIDI & LAUREN: [excited applause]

06:56.365 --> 06:58.233
I'll, uh, go get some glasses.

06:58.334 --> 07:00.535
- Yes!
- About time!

07:00.636 --> 07:06.007
<i>♪</i>

07:06.108 --> 07:07.775
You two are so cute.

07:07.877 --> 07:10.144
I get why cameras wanna
follow you everywhere.

07:10.246 --> 07:12.547
Hey, I think this is about you.

07:12.648 --> 07:14.315
No, Atwood Hedge Funds and Brokerage

07:14.416 --> 07:15.783
is an invite-only hedge fund.

07:15.885 --> 07:18.720
It requires a minimum $10
million investment to join.

07:18.821 --> 07:21.422
WOMAN: Morning TV pays
well, but not that well.

07:21.523 --> 07:23.091
MAN: Not even close.

07:23.192 --> 07:24.492
So, how many zeroes do we think

07:24.593 --> 07:26.327
Mary Jane's producer bae has?

07:26.428 --> 07:27.762
I don't know.

07:27.863 --> 07:30.465
But Miss Mary Jane Paul is
definitely not dating down.

07:30.566 --> 07:33.968
<i>♪</i>

07:34.069 --> 07:36.137
MARY JANE: At least you've
got your own hashtag.

07:36.238 --> 07:37.672
It's not funny.

07:37.773 --> 07:39.674
This is becoming way too intrusive.

07:39.775 --> 07:42.143
I already agreed to
scale it back, didn't I?

07:42.244 --> 07:44.245
Right?

07:44.346 --> 07:46.214
In the larger scheme of things, I mean,

07:46.315 --> 07:50.385
is it really so bad that people
know that you have $30 million?

07:56.659 --> 07:58.660
How did you know it was $30 million?

08:04.199 --> 08:08.102
These so-called journalists
never even saw my statement.

08:08.203 --> 08:09.637
They only saw my in box.

08:09.738 --> 08:12.073
How do you know the exact amount?

08:15.644 --> 08:17.946
Okay, fine! Fine!

08:18.047 --> 08:21.082
Remember when you asked
me to get your passport

08:21.183 --> 08:22.283
for you at your house?

08:22.384 --> 08:26.120
Um... I just... I...
I saw that number...

08:26.221 --> 08:28.957
just lying around your bedroom.

08:29.058 --> 08:31.759
Lying around where?

08:31.860 --> 08:33.461
Well, in a... in a banker's box,

08:33.562 --> 08:36.063
like, up in your... in your closet.

08:36.164 --> 08:37.398
I'm so sorry and it's wrong.

08:37.499 --> 08:39.833
- It's really, really wrong.
- Yet...

08:39.934 --> 08:42.035
- Justin...
- ...you still did it.

08:46.709 --> 08:49.210
♪ Good morning, heartache ♪

08:49.311 --> 08:52.513
♪ You old gloomy sight ♪

08:52.614 --> 08:55.316
♪ Good morning, heartache ♪

08:55.417 --> 08:58.186
♪ Thought we said goodbye last night ♪

08:58.287 --> 08:59.887
HELEN: [sighs]

08:59.989 --> 09:02.523
That old telephone trick?

09:02.624 --> 09:03.825
You're wasting your time.

09:03.926 --> 09:06.961
You're barking up the wrong damn tree.

09:09.565 --> 09:12.000
That old telephone trick?

09:12.101 --> 09:13.534
It's tired.

09:13.635 --> 09:17.171
I only came because I wanted
to tell you to your face.

09:17.272 --> 09:18.573
If you had something to say,

09:18.674 --> 09:20.608
you should have said it 40 years ago.

09:20.709 --> 09:22.377
PAUL SR: What are you
fussin' about, Helen?

09:22.478 --> 09:24.178
Oh?

09:24.279 --> 09:26.014
I forgot to tell you, uh,

09:26.115 --> 09:29.217
I have a Jack & Jane
meeting this morning.

09:29.318 --> 09:31.019
A little early for it, isn't it?

09:31.120 --> 09:32.754
Well, you know Ruby.

09:32.855 --> 09:35.757
We all have to bend to her schedule.

09:37.393 --> 09:39.560
Um... I... I won't be long.

09:42.264 --> 09:44.098
Aren't you forgetting something?

09:47.236 --> 09:49.003
- Oh...
- [laughs]

09:49.104 --> 09:51.239
Oh, thank you, baby.

09:51.340 --> 09:53.608
I won't be long. I promise.

09:53.709 --> 09:57.245
♪ How long can lovers stand ♪

09:57.346 --> 09:59.113
♪ To prove they were right ♪

09:59.214 --> 10:02.583
[door closes]

10:02.684 --> 10:05.686
♪ Why did I fold my hand ♪

10:05.788 --> 10:06.654
Justin?

10:06.755 --> 10:09.123
You have questions about the show?

10:09.224 --> 10:10.892
No.

10:10.993 --> 10:12.894
Then not now.

10:13.996 --> 10:18.299
♪ Who said we had it all ♪

10:18.400 --> 10:21.235
<i>♪</i>

10:21.336 --> 10:23.371
♪ Our hearts no longer lie ♪

10:23.472 --> 10:25.306
AARON: Trouble in paradise?

10:25.407 --> 10:27.241
WOMAN: These are for you.

10:27.342 --> 10:31.079
♪ Who knew the veil would fall ♪

10:31.180 --> 10:34.715
- ♪ Who'd guess that we would cry ♪
