10:49.818 --> 10:51.919
HELEN: That old telephone trick?

10:52.020 --> 10:54.055
These days you could have just texted.

10:54.156 --> 10:55.690
But what fun would that be?

10:55.791 --> 10:56.924
In all honesty,

10:57.025 --> 10:58.759
I was surprised you reached out.

10:58.861 --> 11:00.161
I figured everything had been said

11:00.262 --> 11:02.663
that needed to be said the other night.

11:02.764 --> 11:04.398
Just because you got in the last word

11:04.499 --> 11:06.834
doesn't mean there's
nothing more to be said.

11:06.935 --> 11:08.870
Sit, please?

11:11.206 --> 11:13.307
I do owe you an apology
for leaving Hattiesburg,

11:13.408 --> 11:16.043
and re-enlisting, but that
was 44 years ago, Helen.

11:16.144 --> 11:19.113
You left more than my hometown.

11:19.214 --> 11:21.182
You already know I
regretted leaving you,

11:21.283 --> 11:23.351
but I tried to get you back...

11:23.452 --> 11:24.619
for ten years.

11:24.720 --> 11:25.853
I'd already committed to

11:25.954 --> 11:27.889
making a life with Paul by that time.

11:27.990 --> 11:31.058
- Yeah, I know.
- My best friend.

11:31.159 --> 11:34.795
That's a hard pill to swallow, Helen.

11:34.897 --> 11:36.998
Paul says you put all that behind you.

11:37.099 --> 11:39.367
I did, but that took some time.

11:39.468 --> 11:42.904
I realized that maybe he could give you

11:43.005 --> 11:44.572
the kind of life that you deserve.

11:44.673 --> 11:46.540
But when you came to my hotel room,

11:46.642 --> 11:48.509
demanding an apology...

11:48.610 --> 11:50.978
Did Paul not take care of you?

11:52.247 --> 11:56.017
Frank, Paul and I aren't perfect.

11:56.118 --> 11:58.085
But we are happy.

11:58.186 --> 12:00.955
I made peace with losing you,

12:01.056 --> 12:03.090
and I'm sure you moved on, too.

12:03.191 --> 12:06.227
I did. I created a new life for myself.

12:06.328 --> 12:08.095
I started a successful business,

12:08.196 --> 12:09.730
kept myself busy so I wouldn't have to

12:09.831 --> 12:12.767
think about you all the time.

12:12.868 --> 12:16.003
Time heals all wounds.

12:16.104 --> 12:17.780
But that time...

12:17.937 --> 12:19.707
never came for me.

12:19.808 --> 12:21.676
I think I oughta go.

12:21.777 --> 12:23.210
One request.

12:23.312 --> 12:24.612
Please?

12:24.713 --> 12:25.913
A dance.

12:26.014 --> 12:28.582
This isn't one of our
old nightclubs, Frank.

12:28.684 --> 12:31.485
I don't need a nightclub
to dance with you, Helen.

12:31.586 --> 12:33.254
Please?

12:33.355 --> 12:37.158
<i>♪</i>

12:37.259 --> 12:40.161
KARA: Listen up, everybody.
I need your attention.

12:40.262 --> 12:42.663
WikiLeaks just announced
that they're about to

12:42.764 --> 12:43.798
drop a cache of information

12:43.899 --> 12:46.701
on some very prominent
French politician.

12:46.802 --> 12:48.102
French politician?

12:48.203 --> 12:50.204
Ooh, this could be juicy.

12:50.305 --> 12:52.907
KARA: Yeah, and Garrett
wants a team standing by

12:53.008 --> 12:54.976
so I will be speaking to a few of you

12:55.077 --> 12:56.911
as the day progresses, okay?

12:57.012 --> 12:58.045
I'm here, if you need me.

12:58.146 --> 12:59.613
KARA: Thank you, Emma.

13:00.782 --> 13:02.116
MARY JANE: Hey, Justin,

13:02.217 --> 13:04.018
can I talk to you for a second?

13:05.045 --> 13:06.713
JUSTIN: [sighs]

13:14.229 --> 13:16.163
I feel terrible about all of this.

13:16.264 --> 13:17.565
Let me save you the trouble.

13:17.666 --> 13:18.599
You don't trust me.

13:18.700 --> 13:21.068
No, I do trust you.

13:21.169 --> 13:24.638
Mary Jane, you crawled
into the back of my closet,

13:24.740 --> 13:26.607
and scanned my bank records.

13:26.708 --> 13:27.942
I'm sorry.

13:28.043 --> 13:29.844
How is this relationship
